# ==============================================================================
# ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES - Configuration for Better Auth + Drizzle + Neon
# ==============================================================================
#
# WHY: Environment variables keep sensitive data out of source code and allow
# different configurations per environment (development, staging, production).
#
# WHAT: This file documents all required environment variables for the stack:
#   - DATABASE_URL: Connection string for Neon serverless Postgres
#   - BETTER_AUTH_SECRET: Secret for signing auth tokens/cookies
#   - BETTER_AUTH_URL: Base URL for auth callbacks (OAuth redirects)
#   - OAuth credentials: GitHub and Google provider secrets
#
# DRIZZLE VS PRISMA:
#   - Drizzle: Lightweight, SQL-like syntax, smaller bundle size
#   - Prisma: Larger ecosystem, more abstraction, built-in studio
#   - Drizzle schema lives in TypeScript files (src/db/schema.ts)
#   - Both work excellently with Neon's serverless Postgres
#
# NEON SERVERLESS:
#   - Uses HTTP-based queries (no persistent connections)
#   - Perfect for serverless/edge environments
#   - Drizzle uses @neondatabase/serverless driver
#   - Connection string includes ?sslmode=require
#
# SETUP INSTRUCTIONS:
# 1. Copy this file to .env.local: cp .env.example .env.local
# 2. Get Neon connection string from console.neon.tech
# 3. Generate secret: openssl rand -base64 32
# 4. Configure OAuth at github.com/settings/developers
# 5. Configure OAuth at console.cloud.google.com
#
# FUTURE: Consider adding:
#   - Email provider credentials (Resend, SendGrid)
#   - Rate limiting configuration
#   - Additional OAuth providers
# ==============================================================================

# Database - Neon Serverless Postgres
# Get this from: https://console.neon.tech
# Format: postgresql://user:password@host/database?sslmode=require
DATABASE_URL="postgresql://user:password@ep-xxx.region.aws.neon.tech/neondb?sslmode=require"

# Better Auth Configuration
# Secret: openssl rand -base64 32
BETTER_AUTH_SECRET="your-secret-key-here-generate-with-openssl"
# URL: Your app's base URL (no trailing slash)
BETTER_AUTH_URL="http://localhost:3000"

# OAuth - GitHub
# Create app at: https://github.com/settings/developers
# Callback URL: http://localhost:3000/api/auth/callback/github
GITHUB_CLIENT_ID="your-github-client-id"
GITHUB_CLIENT_SECRET="your-github-client-secret"

# OAuth - Google
# Create credentials at: https://console.cloud.google.com/apis/credentials
# Callback URL: http://localhost:3000/api/auth/callback/google
GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID="your-google-client-id"
GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET="your-google-client-secret"
